```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    return lowercase(replace(col, r"\s+" => "_"))
end
```

This function uses `lowercase` to convert the column name to lowercase and `replace` with a regular expression `r"\s+"` to replace one or more whitespace characters with an underscore. The regex is necessary because in Julia, `\s` matches any whitespace character (including tabs, newlines, etc.), while `\s+` matches one or more occurrences of these characters.
